pageTitle: Louis van Amstel - DWTS - Dancing With The Stars
textBeforeTable: LOUIS VAN AMSTEL ON DANCING WITH THE STARS Louis on Twitter! Follow Louis van Amstel has been a member of the Dancing With The Stars family since its inception. He performed in Season 1 with reality star Trista Rehn (finishing last), and Season 2 with Lisa Rinna (4th), and Season 3 with Monique Coleman (4th), and Season 6 with Priscilla Presley (8th). Louis has also been very involved in choreographing and dancing in group dances on the show. His amazing choreography has been nominated for an Emmy Award. Louis first began dancing in a theatre dance school and later went on to study Classical Dance and Theory at the University of the Arts in Amsterdam. In his competitive dancing career, he has won several titles, including: 7-time Dutch National Amateur Champion, World Amateur Latin Champion ('94, '95), World Professional Showdance Champion ('96), Professional World Latin Finalist ('96) and U.S. National Latin Champion (2000). Louis has used his incredible talents in many fields, such as choreographing for the theatre, appearances on TV shows, and serving as creative director, choreographer, and dancer in the touring Dancing With The Stars show. He also choreographed for Sabrina Bryan in The Cheetah Girls World Tour. He conducts physical fitness
